The paper deals with the conflict-free coloring of geometric intersection graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the categories cs.DM and cs.GT. The paper uses techniques from numerical analysis (cs.NA) to establish lower bounds on the conflict-free chromatic number. Finally, the paper presents algorithms and complexity results, which are relevant to the category cs.DS.
